reviews.reviewText: I bought this so my phone would connect to the CarPlay setting on my car. It worked great for a week or so, then all of a sudden it started having connection issues. The slightest touch/graze will make it disconnect from CarPlay. Some days are better than other but it’s annoying enough where I’m going to just get a new cord.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Let's preface this. I have not run any test to see if the constructions hold up. If the data transfer is true as advertised, or if it can handle I bet high load as a pd. But I have just used it as applied. And it's nice. I prefer a lot of chords and plugs. And we all know and are familiar with the braised lines. But these just 'feel' like quality. Heavy and stiff. With a firm engagement when you insert it. Time will tell. But I am very satisfied witness so far.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Purchased to use for data in a new vehicle. The first cable would charge, but not make a data connection. A replacement cable was sent with the same issue. After that one, I realized that the phone cover was contributing to the issue. It appears that the USB cable that I have been using prior had always worked fine with the same phone cover in place. After the replacement new cable, I found that if I pressed and wiggled the plug at the phone a data connection could be established.Conclusion: The contacts of the new cable plug must be slightly recessed in the plug (in comparison to my original cable) and are not fully making connection when the plug may not be fully seated. Resolution: I carved out some more in my phone cover for the USB port hole. This seems to resolve the connection issue.Otherwise, the cables appear to be quite serviceable. Just be certain that you are able to fully seat the cable plug into your device.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the Netherlands on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: Does not deliver speeds as promised
reviews.reviewText: Got the 10GBPS cable for a samsung 1tb gen 2 SSD drive. Cable does not deliver consitant speed (write speeds very very slow), not even close to 5GBPS. Tried other cables those worked fine. I ordered both and both got the same issue. Cables look and feel very quality but I will use them as charging cables as I do not want to take the hassle of sending them back.If you look for high speed cables gen 3.2 10GBPS, please find another brand is my advise.

In the first glance you can makeout that the image of the product is completely misleading as the image shows a metal braided strong cable with gold-plated connectors. However, the actual one is far from the image. It's nylon braided and regular tin-chromium plated. Second is the performance issue. I use a OnePlus 9 phone with its original 65W charger and original red cable.I tried charging my phone with the cable replaced with the same charger. It is much slower than the original cable that costs Rs.899/- on the OnePlus website. So this cable at a price tag of Rs.789/- is totally NOT worth it.I would like to return this product as I'm not satisfied with its performance and actually quality.
